Drop sprx.o from PSL1GHT liblv2.a.

The sprx.o object inside PSL1GHT's liblv2.a was built from
ppu/sprx/common/exports.S + libexport.c against
ppu/sprx/liblv2/exports.h, which lists ~100 entries from the
`sysPrxForUser` library and emits:

  - one `.lib.stub` Stub record describing the library
  - one `.sceStub.text` trampoline per export
  - one `.rodata.sceFNID` entry per export
  - one `.data.sceFStub` slot per export

The nidgen-emitted liblv2_stub.a now provides the same coverage with
canonical Cell-style names (and PSL1GHT-style aliases for
backwards compatibility).  Linking both produced two `.lib.stub`
Stub records targeting the same library — one of which had stale
import counts after sprx-linker post-link fixup, breaking the
loader's import resolution.

Resolution: drop sprx.o from liblv2.a.  The remaining objects
(thread_wrapper, spu_printf_wrapper, process_wrapper,
spu_thread_printf, sys_spu_wrapper) are PSL1GHT-side helper
wrappers and have no overlap with nidgen.  Their references to
`sysThreadCreateEx`, `sysProcessExitSpawn2Ex`, etc. resolve
against nidgen's trampolines via the standard archive search.

diff --git a/ppu/sprx/liblv2/Makefile b/ppu/sprx/liblv2/Makefile
--- a/ppu/sprx/liblv2/Makefile
+++ b/ppu/sprx/liblv2/Makefile
@@ -76,7 +76,7 @@
 	@cp -frv $(CURDIR)/lib/ppu/*.a $(PSL1GHT)/ppu/lib

 #---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-$(LIBRARY).a: sprx.o thread_wrapper.o spu_printf_wrapper.o process_wrapper.o \
+$(LIBRARY).a: thread_wrapper.o spu_printf_wrapper.o process_wrapper.o \
 			  spu_thread_printf.o sys_spu_wrapper.o
 #---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

